  "time_ut": 1661158078,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0db6\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf\u0db1 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the government intervenes, bakery products can be reduced",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "If the government and related authorities provide necessary support to the bakery owners, the price of a pound of bread can be reduced by Rs. 50/= and the price of other bakery products can be reduced to a significant level and the people can be relieved, said the President of All Lanka Bakery Owners' Association N.K. Says Jayawardena.",
        "The prices of flour, sugar, margarine and eggs, which are the main ingredients required for bakery production, have been greatly reduced.",
        "Mr. Jayawardena said that due to the dollar problem, the price of bakery products in the market has gone up a lot and said that a bread mafia is also operating in the country.",
        "He also mentioned that the bakery owners have to get bread for 280 rupees due to the mafia, which can be given for 200 rupees.",
        "He said that the price of eggs has also increased unfairly, and even though the government has imposed a control price on eggs, eggs are not available in the market at the control price.",
        "If we get the support of the government and the authorities, the price of 400 grams of bread, which has a high price of Rs. 190/=, can be reduced by Rs. 50/= per pound, a bun sold at the price of Rs. 100/= by Rs. 25/= and also the price of other bakery products can be reduced by a significant amount. Mr. Jayawardena had stated that.",
        "He also emphasized that if the government does not intervene and provide support to this problem, there may be a referendum in the country not to buy bakery products, just as there was a referendum in the country not to eat biscuits."
      ],
